881. crastini (locative) = crastino, cf. die septimi Pers. 260, Men. 1156. Gellius (X. 24- 1 ff.) says that diequinti or diequinte (pronounced as one word) = ‘ on the fifth day ’ was the regular phrase in the time of Cicero ; and quotes as similar expressions die pristini, die proximi, die crastini ; cf. postri-dz'e :postero die, διο.
